news.title: Ahmedabad civic body seals 599 properties over property tax default
news.para: The tax and revenue department sealed a total of 2,358 properties in the last one week for defaulting on payment of tax despite repeated notices, a statement from the Ahmedabad Municipal Corporation said.

news.title: Indore civic body to crackdown on illegal colonies from February 15
news.para: IMC commissioner Pratibha Pal on Tuesday reviewed the status of works related to the colony cell and instructed officials to launch a crackdown against illegal colonies to remove illegal structures as part of its anti-encroachment drive.

news.title: Stilt plus four floor buildings cannot be constructed in Panchkula: Haryana government
news.para: When asked if such a ban would be applicable on Panchkula or the entire state, Gian Chand Gupta, speaker, Haryana assembly said it is for Panchkula city only. He, however, added a formal order mentioning all conditions and area of operation may be released within two days.

news.title: Mehrauli demolition: Delhi HC orders authorities to maintain status quo till Feb 16
news.para: ​The high court also asked the Delhi Development Authority (DDA) to state its stand on a batch of petitions challenging the demolition action and seeking a bar on demolition in the Mehrauli Archaeological Park area in south Delhi till a fresh "demarcation report" has been prepared.

news.title: Axis-Tishman Speyer's commercial realty platform secures Rs 400 crore first close
news.para: Through this first-ever alliance in the country between a fund house and an international real estate major, Axis Asset Management Co is raising up to '1,500 crore including a green-shoe option, while Tishman Speyer will act as the exclusive development manager for the platform.

news.title: Gurugram: Two more towers in Chintels Paradiso declared unsafe
news.para: ​Towers E and F of the society in Sector 109 are not fit for habitation, Additional Deputy Commissioner (ADC) Vishram Kumar Meena said, adding that the IIT-Delhi team completed the sampling work of towers A and G while the same for Tower H is in progress.

news.title: No 'coercive action' till March 15 against DLF: Allahabad HC
news.para: Following a Supreme Court order of May last year, the Authority had on December 1 handed Rs 295 crore to Reddy Veerana, who owned 7,400sqm in Chhalera Bangar village.

news.title: Greater Noida: GNIDA seals 11 unsold flats in MSX Alpha Homes over Rs 18 crore dues
news.para: The builder, officials said, had not provided basic facilities to 160 families residing in the society and got registries of the flats done. There are 187 flats in the residential society, of which 11 are unsold.

news.title: Special officials must under PMLA for estate agents with Rs 20 lakh turnover: MahaRERA
news.para: The principal officer would act as a central reference point in facilitating reporting of suspicious transactions and identify potentially suspicious transactions.

news.title: Blackstone says India top Asian market, eyes infra investments
news.para: Private equity deals in India totalled $32 billion last year, a 27% drop from 2021. However India's share of total Asia funding rose to 25% from 16% in the same period.

news.title: Shriram Properties' net profit increases by 69.27% in Q3 FY23
news.para: Shriram Properties' consolidated total income from operations stood at Rs 222.01 crore in Q3 FY23, a growth of 70.62 per cent from Rs 130.12 crore it recorded in the similar quarter of the last year.

news.title: NBCC's net profit dips 17.40% in Q3 FY23
news.para: NBCC's consolidated total income from operations stood at Rs 2,191.24 crore in Q3 FY23, a growth of 7.27 per cent from Rs 2,042.79 crore it recorded in the similar quarter of the last year.

news.title: Poddar Housing & Development posts net loss of Rs 9.39 crore in Q3 FY23
news.para: The board of directors of Poddar Housing & Development approved and recommended the sale/disposal off their project 'Poddar Riveria' situated at Mahral, Kalyan to Runwal Developers by way of slump sale.

news.title: Ashiana Housing posts net profit of Rs 9.05 crore in Q3 FY23
news.para: Ashiana Housing's consolidated total income stood at Rs 135.31 crore in Q3 FY23, a growth of 110.80 per cent from Rs 64.19 crore it recorded in the similar quarter of the last year.

news.title: Prestige Estates Projects' net profit up 75% in Q3 FY23
news.para: Prestige Estates Projects' consolidated total revenue stood at Rs 2,347.50 crore in Q3 FY23, a growth of 74.22 per cent from Rs 1,347.40 crore it recorded in the similar quarter of the last year.
